text: The Eastern Region (, also known as Austfirðir: "Eastfjords") is a region in the east of the Iceland. The population of the region was 15,300 (2007). The biggest town in the region is Egilsstaðir, with a population of 2,300. The oldest municipality is Djúpivogur. == Related pages == * Regions of Iceland Category:Regions of Iceland
